To run the application.
Open CMD and move into the folder of the project.
Open the Virtual manager devicer from Android Studio and start the virtual mobile.
In the CMD type "npm start"
When it is running press "A" to connect to the virtual mobile device.


Run server:
change into C:\Users\Bruger\Desktop\Bachelor\backend
Run command: node index.js in terminal


Google Cloud:
1. Open "Google Cloud SDK Shell"
2. Run command: "gcloud auth login"
3. Login through website that opens
4. Validate the current running project or use command: "gcloud config set project chatbotbachelor"
5. Generate access token: "gcloud auth print-access-token"

curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/ask-question -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"question\": \"What is the capital of France?\"}"






